pell</i> ‘hat, hood’, as a nickname for someone who habitually wore a hat or hood, or a metonymic occupational name for someone who made hats or hoods."]},{"name":"Capeles","meanings":["Hispanic (Puerto Rico): probably the plural form of Catalan   Capel  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Capel was born in 1398, in Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, England, his father, Sir John Capel, was 21 and his mother, Elizabeth De Creedy, was 21. He married Joan De Ros about 1445, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died before 14 June 1449, in Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, and was buried in Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"1398–Bef 14 June 1449":"1398–enne 14. juunit 1449","1398–1449":"1398–1449","1422–Female":"1422–Surnud","1446–1515":"1446–1515","1446–Male":"1446–Surnud","1377–Male":"1377–Surnud","1377–Female":"1377–Surnud","1446":"1446","1422":"1422","1377":"1377","1398":"1398","Bef 14 June 1449":"enne 14. juunit 1449","about 1445":"umbes 1445","1449":"1449","1515":"1515","Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, England","Stoke By Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1398–Bef 14 June 1449":"1398–ennen vuotta 14. kesäkuuta 1449","1398–1449":"1398–1449","1422–Female":"1422–Kuollut","1446–1515":"1446–1515","1446–Male":"1446–Kuollut","1377–Male":"1377–Kuollut","1377–Female":"1377–Kuollut","1446":"1446","1422":"1422","1377":"1377","1398":"1398","Bef 14 June 1449":"ennen vuotta 14. kesäkuuta 1449","about 1445":"noin 1445","1449":"1449","1515":"1515","Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, England","Stoke By Nayland, Suffolk, England":"Stoke by Nayland, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"1398–Bef 14 June 1449":"1398–avant 14 juin 1449","1398–144